    "Aperture is the opening used to collect the reflected energy and form an image.",
    "Interferometric Synthetic Aperture Radar (InSAR) is a geodetic radar technique for remote sensing applications generating maps of deformation on surfaces or digital elevations by comparing two or more SAR images.SAR techniques stand out for their simple design process, their flexibility to change any scanning scheme, and the high computation efficiency for processing.",
    "However, data acquisition is generally slow, many antenna pairs or scan positions are required and are more suitable for stationary or slowly moving targets.",
    "It should be noted here that mm-Wave radars in general, e.g.",
    "Multi-input Multi-output (MIMO) [66] can be used for (range, azimuth and elevation) point cloud generation to detect moving targets."
  ],
